def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)

    if isinstance(key, (list, tuple)):
        groupings = []
        exclusions = []

        if axis == 1:
            for k in key:
                try:
                    gpr = obj[k]
                    ping = Grouping(
                        group_axis,
                        gpr,
                        obj=obj,
                        name=k,
                        level=None,
                        sort=sort,
                        observed=observed,
                        in_axis=True,
                    )
                    groupings.append(ping)
                    exclusions.append(k)
                except KeyError:
                    raise KeyError(f"Column name '{k}' not found in the DataFrame")

            grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort, mutated=mutated)
            return grouper, exclusions, obj
